es]]\n|[[Pellissier Building and Wiltern Theatre|Wiltern Theater]]\n|-\n|16 April 2016\n|[[San Francisco]]\n|[[Warfield Theatre|Warfield Theater]]\n|-\n|17 April 2016\n|[[Seattle]]\n|[[The Showbox|Showbox Sodo]]\n|-\n|23 July 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Shanghai]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" |China<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sedaily.com/NewsView/1KYQIEWEV5/GH0302|title=AOMG, \uc911\uad6d \uc0c1\ud574 \uacf5\uc5f0 \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 2\ucd08 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4\u2026\ud799\ud569 \ud55c\ub958 \uc5f4\ub9ac\ub098|date=2016-07-04|website=Seoul Economic Daily|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |QSW Culture Center\n|-\n|24 July 2016\n|-\n|24 September 2016\n|[[Guangzhou]]\n|Guangzho International Trade Center\n|}\n'''Follow The Movement Tour 2017'''\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:250px;\"|Venue\n|-\n|11 February 2017\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Seoul]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |South Korea<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=241784|title=\ud45c\ubbf8\ub0b4 \uae30\uc790 - AOMG \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \u20182017 Follow The Movement\u2019 \uc131\ub8cc|last=|first=|date=2017-02-14|work=Top Star News|access-date=2018-04-22|language=ko}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Olympic Hall]]\n|-\n|12 February 2017\n|-\n|25 March 2017\n|[[Bangkok]]\n|Thailand\n|BCC Hall Central Plaza Ladprao\n|-\n|9 April 2017\n|[[Taipei]]\n|Taiwan\n|[[Taipei International Convention Center]]\n|-\n|1 May 2017\n|[[Singapore]]\n|Singapore\n|[[Suntec Singapore Convention and Exhibition Centre|Suntec Singapore Convention]] \n[[Suntec Singapore Convention and Exhibition Centre|and Exhibition Centre]]\n|-\n|16 December 2017\n|[[Macau]]\n|Macau\n|Studio City Event Center\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n* Elle Style Award (Best Music Act)\n\n== Signhere ==\n''Signhere'' aims to discover new artists with a wide range of talents in rap, vocal, music production and also the capabilities of performing for AOMG. AOMG joins hand with the TV channel MBN to showcase the audition project program. The artist who wins in the audition will be signed with a three-year contract with AOMG. It is airs on MBN every Thursday at 9:30 p.m. KST starting from 22 August 2019. \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.aomgofficial.com/}}\n\n{{CJ E&M Music and Live}}\n{{commons category|AOMG}}\n\n[[Category:South Korean hip hop record labels]]\n[[Category: Talent agencies of South Korea]]\n[[Category:Labels distributed by Kakao M]]\n[[Category: Labels distributed by CJ E&M Music and Live]]\n[[Category: CJ E&M Music and Live subsidiaries]]\n[[Category: CJ E&M Music Performance Division]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=September 2016}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=September 2016}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox record label\n| name = AOMG\n| image = AOMG (Above Average Music Group) logo.jpg\n| image_size = <!-- size -->\n| image_alt = The logo of AOMG\n| caption = The logo of AOMG\n| founded = {{start date|2013}}\u2013present\n| founder = [[Jay Park]]\n| distributor = \n| genre = [[Hip Hop music|Hip Hop]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| country = South Korea\n| url = {{Official website|aomgofficial.com}}\n| parent = [[CJ E&M]]\n}}\n'''AOMG''' is a South Korean [[Hip hop music|hip-hop]] and [[R&B]] record label founded in 2013 by singer, songwriter, and rapper [[Jay Park]].<ref name=\":2\" /> The label represents various music artists such as [[Loco (rapper)|Loco]], [[Gray (singer)|Gray]], [[Simon Dominic]], [[Hoody (singer)|Hoody]], [[Woo Won-jae]], [[Code Kunst]], Sogumm, [[Punchnello]], and DeVita, as well as other entities such as UFC fighter [[Chan Sung Jung]] (The Korean Zombie).  <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/8466296/jay-park-ask-bout-me-capsule-yacht-video-interview|title=Jay Park Talks 'Ask Bout Me' Capsule, 'Yacht' Video With Vic Mensa & More|last=Diep|first=Eric|date=2018-07-20|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nAbove Ordinary Music Group (AOMG) is a prominent Korean hip-hop and R&B record label originating from the \"Art of Movement,\" a Seattle-based B-Boying group which [[Jay Park]] joined in 2003, featuring members such as Dial Tone, Junior, and [[Cha Cha Malone]].\nJay Park founded AOMG in late September 2013, and initially signed composer Jun Goon, singer and producer [[Gray (singer)|Gray]], and Seattle affiliate Cha Cha Malone, who was a producer and dancer with [[Jay Park]]'s dance crew [[Art of Movement]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2013/09/jay-park-establishes-independent-label-aomg|title=Jay Park establishes independent label 'AOMG'|date=2013-09-23|website=Allkpop|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> The label had its launch party on October 10, 2013, at \"The A\" in Seoul with Ben Baller as the host.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2013/10/09/jay-park-to-kick-off-launch-party-for-his-independent-label-aomg/|title=Jay Park to Kick Off Launch Party For His Independent Label \"AOMG\"|date=2013-10-09|website=Soompi|accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref> The same month, the label released its first album, Gray's mini-album, ''Call Me Gray''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2013/10/26/jay-park-introduces-new-artist-gray-and-their-agency-aomg/|title=Jay Park Introduces New Artist Gray and Their Agency AOMG|date=2013-10-26|website=Soompi|accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref>\n\nArtists [[Elo (singer)|Elo]], [[Loco (rapper)|Loco]], [[Ugly Duck (rapper)|Ugly Duck]], DJ Wegun, DJ Pumkin, and [[Hoody (singer)|Hoody]] joined AOMG over the next two years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://officiallykmusic.com/the-first-woman-to-join-the-aomg-is-rb-singer-hoody-kim/|title=The First Woman To Join AOMG Is R&B Singer, Hoody Kim|date=2015-12-16|website=Officially Kmusic|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2014, [[Simon Dominic]] announced that he had joined AOMG as co-CEO several months after his departure from his former label [[Amoeba Culture]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/82859/20140309/simon-d-joins-aomg.htm|title=Simon D Goes Solo - Former Supreme Team Member Joins Jay Park's New Label AOMG|date=2014-03-09|website=KpopStarz|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> \n\nIn January 2016, South Korean media company [[CJ E&M]] announced that it had formed a strategic partnership with AOMG.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hellokpop.com/news/cj-em-partners-with-jay-parks-label-aomg/|title=CJ E&M Partners With Jay Park\u2019s Label AOMG|date=2016-01-06|website=HelloKpop|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref> CJ E&M said in a statement that it would \"support\" AOMG with distribution and marketing, while AOMG would continue to control its music.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160106001137|title=CJ E&M acquires hip-hop label AOMG|last=Won|first=Ho-jung|date=2016-01-06|website=The Korean Herald|access-date=2016-03-25}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2018, Simon Dominic announced his resignation from his position as co-CEO with his song \"Me No Jay Park\". It was later clarified by AOMG that Dominic would remain as an artist on the label. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2018/07/simon-d-resigns-as-co-ceo-of-aomg|title=Simon D resigns as co-CEO of AOMG|date=2018-07-25|website=allkpop|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> \n\nIn August 2019, AOMG\u2019s first hip-hop audition show ''Signhere'' began airing on MBN, marking the first ever hip-hop and R&B record label to have their own audition program on broadcast television. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hellokpop.com/news/aomg-audition-program-signhere/|title=AOMG Prepares For K-Hip Hop\u2019s Next Big Names With Teasers For \u201cSignhere\u201d Audition Program|date=2019-12-09|website=hellokpop|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref> The show lasted 10 episodes, with singer-songwriter Sogumm winning the audition and subsequently joining AOMG as an official label member. \n\n<br /> \n[[File:AOMG 11152014 17.jpg|thumb|right|[[Jay Park]], [[Simon Dominic]], [[Gray (singer)|Gray]], [[Loco (rapper)|Loco]] - 2014 United States Tour]][[File:AOMG 11152014 15.jpg|thumb|right|[[Loco (rapper)|Loco]] and [[Jay Park]] - 2014 United States Tour]]\n\n== Key people ==\n\n*[[Jay Park]] <small>(Founder & CEO)</small>\n\n*DJ Pumkin <small>(Co-CEO 2018 - present)</small>\n*[[Simon Dominic]] <small>(Co-CEO 2014 - 2018)</small>\n\n== Roster ==\n===Current artists===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Act\n! Year <br>signed\n! Releases <br>under the label\n|-\n| [[Jay Park]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 8\n|-\n| [[Cha Cha Malone]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | -\n|-\n| [[Gray (singer)|Gray]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n|-\n| [[Loco (rapper)|Loco]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 4\n|-\n| [[Simon Dominic]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 3\n|-\n| [[Elo (singer)|Elo]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2\n|-\n| [[Ugly Duck (rapper)|Ugly Duck]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n|-\n| [[Hoody (singer)|Hoody]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2015\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2\n|-\n| [[Woo Won-jae]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2017\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n|-\n| [[Code Kunst]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2018\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2\n|-\n| Junior Chef <small>(Under Record Contract)</small>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | -\n|-\n| Sogumm\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | -\n|-\n| [[Punchnello]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n|-\n| DeVita\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 2020\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | 1\n|}\n\n====Other Notable Figures====\n*DJ {{Not a typo|Pumkin}}\n*DJ Wegun\n*[[Chan Sung Jung]] (The Korean Zombie) <small>(2018-present)</small>\n\n== Collaborations ==\nAOMG has had multiple collaborations with dance crews and studios including:\n\n*1MILLION Dance Studio\n**\"All I Wanna Do (K)\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Hoody & Loco)</span> \n**\"Yacht (K)\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring [[Sik-K]])</span>\n\n*Prepix\n**\"Me Like Yuh (K)\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Hoody)</span>\n**\"Yacht (K)\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Sik-K)</span>\n*PURPLOW <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/purplow2011|title=PURPLOW_FACEBOOK|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n**\"Thinking About You\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Loco featuring Jay Park)</span>\n**\"Mommae\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Ugly Duck)</span>\n**\"You Know\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Okasian)</span>\n**\"Ain't No Party Like An AOMG Party\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park & Ugly Duck)</span>\n**\"Me Like Yuh (K)\" <br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Jay Park featuring Hoody)</span>\n\n== Discography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!Year\n!Album title\n!Artist\n!Ref.\n|-\n|2013\n|''Call Me Gray''\n|[[Gray (singer)|Gray]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20131208000170|title=Producer-turned-rapper wants everyone to know his name|last=Kalka|first=Emma|date=2013-12-08|website=The Korea Herald|language=en|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|''Evolution''\n|[[Jay Park]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6243940/jay-park-evolution-album-so-good-promise|title=Jay Park Showcases His Rapping & Singing 'Evolution' on Strong Sophomore LP|last=Oak|first=Jessica|last2=Benjamin|first2=Jeff|date=2014-09-06|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Locomotive''\n|[[Loco (rapper)|Loco]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.joins.com/article/22491292|title=\ub85c\uaf2c, \ub370\ubdd4 \uccab \ub2e8\ub3c5 \ucf58\uc11c\ud2b8 \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 1\ubd84 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \uc804\uc11d \ub9e4\uc9c4|date=2018-03-30|website=JoongAng Ilbo|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2015\n|''Won & Only''\n|[[Simon Dominic]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/641103|title=\uc0ac\uc774\uba3c \ub3c4\ubbf8\ub2c9, '\uc6d0\uc564\uc628\ub9ac'\ub85c \uc74c\uc6d0 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uc811\uc218 '2\uc5f0\ud0c0 \ud648\ub7f0'|date=2015-08-21|website=Ten Asia|language=ko-KR|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Worldwide''\n|Jay Park\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cctoday.co.kr/?mod=news&act=articleView&idxno=935877|title=\ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94 \uc0c8\uc568\ubc94\uc740 \ud799\ud569 \ucef4\ud544\ub808\uc774\uc158?\u2026\ub798\ud37c 27\uba85 \ud53c\ucc98\ub9c1|date=2015-10-30|website=Chungcheong Today|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2016\n|''Scene Stealers''\n|Jay Park & [[Ugly Duck (rapper)|Ugly Duck]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asiatoday.co.kr/view.php?key=20160712001122059|title=\ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94X\uc5b4\uae00\ub9ac\ub355, \u2018\uc6b0\ub9ac\uac00 \ube60\uc9c0\uba74 PARTY\uac00 \uc544\ub2c8\uc9c0\u2019 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026AOMG \ucf5c\ub77c\ubcf4|date=2016-07-13|website=Asia Today|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|''8 Femmes''\n|[[Elo (singer)|Elo]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mk.co.kr/news/entertain/view/2016/08/597829/|title=ELO(\uc5d8\ub85c), \ubc15\uc7ac\ubc94\uacfc \ud568\uaed8\ud55c \u2018\ud0c0\ud22c(Tattoo)\u2019 \uc120\uacf5\uac1c|date=2016-08-23|website=Maeil Business Newspaper|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Everything You Wanted''\n