rticle/23562272|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u00b7\ubc15\uc131\uc6c5, OCN '\ub8e8\uac08' \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5|last=\uc785\ub825 2019.08.26 17:31|date=2019-08-26|website=\uc911\uc559\uc77c\ubcf4|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newspim.com/news/view/20200327000787|title='\ub8e8\uac08' '\ucee4\ubba4\ub2c8\ud2f0' '\uc624\uc790\ud06c3'\u2026\ub137\ud50c\ub9ad\uc2a4, \uc774\ubc88\uc8fc \uc2e0\uc791 \ub77c\uc778\uc5c5 \uacf5\uac1c|date=2020-03-27|website=\ub274\uc2a4\ud54c|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nKang Ki-beom ([[Choi Jin-hyuk]]) is an elite police officer whose custody of the Argos, a nationwide criminal organization, results in a group of masked murderers from Argos killing his beloved wife and cutting both eyes. Kang wakes up in a town only to find himself having nothing to do with killing his family members. The NIS approached him as a member of Rugal, an expert team organized by the NIS. He received two artificial eyes with Rugal's biotechnology instructing them and with them unique new studies that would reduce criminal organizations. Kang Ki-beom and Rugal are walking through a life to capture the Argos. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hankyung.com/entertainment/article/202004123422I|title='\ub8e8\uac08' \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \uc8fd\uc774\uae30 \uc704\ud574 \ub098\ud0c0\ub09c \u2018\uc2e4\ud5d8\uccb4\u2019 \uae40\ub2e4\ud604|date=2020-04-12|website=hankyung.com|language=ko|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Choi Jin-hyuk]] as Kang Gi-bum\n* [[Park Sung-woong]] as Hwang Deuk-goo\n* [[Park Sun-ho]] as Lee Gwang-cheol\n* Jung Hye-in as Song Mi-na\n* [[Jo Dong-hyuk]] as Han Tae-woong\n* Kim Min-sang as Choi Geun-cheol\n* Han Ji Wan as Choi Ye-won\n\n===Supporting===\n* [[Jang In-sub]] as Bradley, Rugal's mechanic.\n* Jang Seo-kyung as Susan\n* Park Choong-seon as Section Chief Oh\n* Yoo Sang-hoon as Min Dal-ho, Argos acting leader.\n* Park Jung-hak as Go Yong-deok