52|UB M52]]\n| [[File:Teski minobacac 120 mm UB M52 2011 7242.jpg|150px]]\n| [[Mortar (weapon)|120mm Mortar]]\n| {{flag|Yugoslavia}}\n| less than 95\n|According to the ''Future Artillery Systems: 2016 Market Report'', there are total 95 120mm mortars including Brandt F1,UB M52.<ref name=\"Arty2016\"/>\n|-\n| [[Type 87 mortar|Type 87]]\n| [[File:Zagan 82 mm mo\u017adzierz wz 37.jpg|150px]]\n| [[Mortar (weapon)|82mm Mortar]]\n| [[File:Flag of the People's Republic of China.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| 300+\n| <ref name=\"Arty2016\"/>\n|-\n|-\n| [[M29 mortar|M29]]\n| [[File:Mortar M29.jpg|150px]]\n| [[Mortar (weapon)|81mm Mortar]]\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 11\n| ''M29A1'' variant.<ref name=\"Arty2016\"/>\n|-\n| [[M2 mortar#Chinese variants|Type 63-1]]\n| [[File:No-image-available.png|150px]]\n| [[Mortar (weapon)|60mm Mortar]]\n| [[File:Flag of the People's Republic of China.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| \n| {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n|-\n| Type 93\n| [[File:No-image-available.png|150px]]\n| [[Mortar (weapon)|60mm Mortar]]\n| [[File:Flag of the People's Republic of China.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| \n| {{cn|date=January 2020}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Tanks==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! width=16%| Name\n! width=21%| Image\n! width=15%| Type\n! width=12%| Origin\n! width=10%| Quantity\n! width=26%| Notes\n|-\n| [[Al-Khalid tank#Production variants|MBT-2000/VT-1A]]\n| [[File:Bangladesh Army MBT2000. (39072813711).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Main battle tank]]\n| {{CHN}}\n| 44\n| <ref name=\"SIPRI\"/>\n|-\n| [[Type 69 tank#Bangladesh|Type 69-IIG]]\n| [[File:Bangladesh Army T-69 IIG (24449169416).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Main battle tank]]\n| {{CHN}}\n| 58\n| 58 [[Type 69 tank|Type 69-IIA tanks]] upgraded to [[Type 69 tank#Bangladesh|Type 69-IIG]] version with kits from China in 2010-2013.<ref name=\"SIPRI\" />\n|-\n| [[Type 59G(BD) Durjoy]]\n| [[File:Bangladesh Army upgraded T-59G 'Durjoy' MBT. (33659625935).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Main battle tank]]\n| {{BAN}}