ing |date= February 2013|title=brief 47 |url=https://www.bicc.de/uploads/tx_bicctools/BICC_brief_02.pdf |publisher=Bonn International Center for Conversion |page=159|issn=0947-7322|access-date=8 September 2019 |quote=\"MANPADS A Terrorist Threat to Civilian Aviation?\" }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[HQ-7#HQ-7A (FM-90)|FM-90]]\n| |[[File:Bangladesh Army FM90 Crotale SAM. (38169460305).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Short range air defense|SHORAD]]\n| [[File:Flag of China.png|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| 2 regiments\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=FM-90 missiles join Bangladesh Army\u2019s anti-air defence |url=http://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2017/01/03/fm-90-missiles-army/ |url-status=live |newspaper=The Dhaka Tribune |date=3 January 2017 |access-date=22 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222220117/http://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2017/01/03/fm-90-missiles-army/ |archive-date=22 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\"| [[Anti-aircraft guns]]\n|-\n| [[37 mm automatic air defense gun M1939 (61-K)#Variants|Type 65/74]]\n| [[File:Bangladesh Army Air Defence Artillery 37mm T-74 (23848577803).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Autocannon|37mm Autocannon]]\n| [[File:Flag of China.png|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| 132\n| {{sfn|The Military Balance 2016|p=236}}\n|-\n| [[AZP S-60|Type-59]]\n| [[File:S-60.jpg|150px]]\n| [[Autocannon|57mm Autocannon]]\n| [[File:Flag of China.png|frameless|23x23px]] [[China]]\n| 34\n| According to ''The Military Balance 2017'' by [[International Institute for Strategic Studies|IISS]]{{sfn|The Military Balance 2017|p=274}} \n|-\n| [[Oerlikon GDF#Versions|Oerlikon GDF]]\n| [[File:GDF Ej\u00e9rcito espa\u00f1ol.jpg|150px]]\n| [[Autocannon|35mm Autocannon]]\n| {{SWI}}\n| 4\n| GDF-009 variant.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=NEWLY ADDITION IN BANGLADESH ARMY ORELIKON RADAR CONTROLLED GUN TEST FIRING HELD AT COXBAZAR|url=https://www.ispr.gov.bd/en/newly-addition-in-bangladesh-army-orelikon-radar-controlle