at\n|[[File:Bangladesh Army 'Sea Horse' utility boat. (38338544996).jpg|150px]]\n| Sea Horse-1 <br> Sea Horse-2\n| [[File:Flag of Bangladesh.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[Bangladesh]]\n| \n| The 14.50 meters Boat can carry 20 troops.Two Seahorses were successfully delivered to Bangladesh Army on 13 November 2017. The handover ceremony was held in Dockyard and Engineering Works Ltd.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://metacentre.com.bd/seahorse.html| title=Metacentre-seahorse| website=Metacentre| accessdate= 2 May 2019|url-status=live| df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Aircraft==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! width=16%| Aircraft\n! width=21%| Image\n! width=15%| Type\n! width=12%| Origin\n! width=10%| Quantity\n! width=26%| Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\"| [[Fixed-wing aircraft|Fixed-wing Aircraft]]\n|-\n| [[Cessna 208 Caravan|Cessna 208B Grand Caravan]]\n| [[File:S3-BMJ Bangladesh Army Aviation Cessna 208. (34003750594).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Utility aircraft]]\n| [[File:Flag of United States.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[United States]]\n| 1\n| <ref name=\"flightglobal\">{{cite book |date=2019 |title=World Air Forces 2019 |url=https://www.flightglobal.com/asset/26019/waf/ |url-access=registration |publisher=Flightglobal Insight |page=11 |access-date=21 April 2019}}</ref><br />IISS 2011 also list one [[Piper PA-31T Cheyenne]] (IISS 2011, 226)\n|-\n| [[Cessna 152|Cessna 152 Aerobat]]\n| [[File:S3-BML Bangladesh Army Aviation Cessna 152 (23495359043).jpg|150px]]\n| [[Light aircraft]]\n| {{USA}}\n| 5\n| ''A152 Aerobat'' Variant.<ref name=\"ISPR\">{{cite web |url= https://www.ispr.gov.bd/en/training-aircraft-inducted-in-bangladesh-army/|title = Training Aircraft Inducted In Bangladesh Army |publisher= ISPR|date=12 December 2019 |accessdate= 12 December 2019}}</ref> According to ''The Military Balance 2017'' by [[International Institute for Strategic Studies|IISS]]{{sfn|The Military Balance 2017|p=274}} \n|-\n| [[Diamond DA40#Variants|DA40NG]]\n| [[File:Diamond DA.40NG \u2018G-S