4 truck\n| [[File:Flag of Japan.svg|frameless|23x23px]] [[Japan]]\n| \n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Field Kitchen Units==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! width=16%| Name\n! width=21%| Image\n! width=15%| Type\n! width=12%| Origin\n! width=10%| Quantity\n! width=26%| Notes\n|-\n| AHB-2,5|| [[File:Bangladesh Army Mobile Field Bakery System with Zil-137 tractor. (39311065191).jpg|200px]] || Mobile Field Bakery System || {{UKR}} ||  || \n|}\n\n==Attire==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! width=16%| Name\n! width=21%| Pattern name(s)\n! width=15%| Pattern\n! width=12%| Images\n! width=26%| Notes\n|-\n| Combat Uniform\n| [[U.S. Woodland|Woodland]] \n| [[File:\"M81\" U.S. woodland camouflage pattern swatch.png|125px]] \n| [[File:Modular Infantry Bangladesh Army (23445743710).jpg|125px]] [[File:Woman officer of Bangladesh Army at Unnayan Mela 2018 in Comilla.jpg|125px]]\n|Emerging in the 1990s, a very brightly-colored woodland-style pattern came into use with Bangladeshi forces. Although similar to the US design, the shapes appear to be based on different drawings. This design is still in use today, although the colors have been changed a little from older versions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://camopedia.org/index.php?title=Bangladesh|title=Bangladesh|work=Camopedia}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bangladesh Army]]\n* [[East Bengal Regiment]]\n* [[Bangladesh Infantry Regiment]]\n* [[Bangladesh Army Aviation Group]]\n* [[List of active Bangladesh military aircraft]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* {{cite book|title=The Military Balance 2016|date=February 2016|volume=116|isbn=9781857438352 |publisher=Routlegde|ref={{harvid|The Military Balance 2016}}|author=International Institute for Strategic Studies|author-link=International Institute for Strategic Studies}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n{{Commons category|Equipment of the Bangladesh Army}}\n* [http://www.army.mil.bd/ Official Website of Bangladesh Army]\n* [http://lcweb2.loc.gov/cgi-bin/query/r?frd/